(1) Whenever it appears to the President necessary or expedient— (a) to control the import into or export from Zambia of any goods ; (b) to control the distribution, disposal, purchase and sale or the wholesale or retail prices of any commodity or animal and the charges which may be made— (i) for the services relating to distribution, disposal, purchase and sale of the commodity or animal , as the case may be; and (ii) for the delivery of any commodity or animal , the wholesale or retail prices of which are controlled under this section; (c) to prevent the hoarding of any goods , commodities or animals; and (d) to regulate the charges for any controlled services; he may, by Statutory Instrument, make such regulations as appear to him to be necessary or expedient for such purposes.
